Thank you for downloading sebsocket server. This is the READEME file comes with WebSocket server.

For the latest version of websocket server visit http://github.com/narup/websocket


What is websocket?
websocket is a simple statndalone java based HTML5 websocket server API implementation. It is a very simple implementation so that java developers can play around with HTML5 Web Socket based applications or prototype application without taking a hassle of setting up any servers.

Licensing.

This is free and anyone can do anything with this code.


Documentation

No real documentation yet, trying to come up with a working example.


Installing 
Just download the jar from http://github.com/narup/websocket and put it in your classpath

Usage
1. Implement WebSocketHandler Interface and write your application code on the appropriate webscoket events 
2. Run the server as java StartWebSocketServer -config path-to-config-file

example of config file:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<websocket xmlns="http://dev.w3.org/html5/websockets/">
	<configurations>
		<host>websocket-server</host>
		<port>8080</port>
		<documentRoot>/</documentRoot>
	</configurations>
	<handlers>
		<handler>
			<handlerName>com.jwebsocket.example.TestHandler</handlerName>
			<properties>
				<property>
					<key>appName</key>
					<value>TestHandler</value>
				</property>
			</properties>
		</handler>
	</handlers>
</websocket>



References:
http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-hixie-thewebsocketprotocol-68 - The Web Socket protocol
http://dev.w3.org/html5/websockets/ - HTML5 web socket API description
http://mina.apache.org/ - Apache MINA framework
  

